            <entry xml:id="entry_æxsærʒæn" xml:lang="os">
                <form xml:id="form_d1026e66" type="lemma"><orth>æxsærʒæn</orth></form>
                <sense xml:id="sense_d1026e69"><abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                        <q>водопад</q>
                    </abv:tr><abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                        <q>waterfall</q>
                    </abv:tr></sense>
                <abv:exampleGrp>
                    <abv:example xml:id="example_d1026e81">
                        <quote>don kæly jæ ræzty ūrs æxsærʒæntæj</quote>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                            <q>река льется перед ним белыми водопадами</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                            <q>the river is flowing in front of them like white waterfalls</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_Коста"/><biblScope>63</biblScope></bibl>
                    </abv:example>
                    <abv:example xml:id="example_d1026e100">
                        <quote>æxsærʒæny qazt</quote>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                            <q>игра водопада</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                            <q>the waterfall's game</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_Коста"/><biblScope>49</biblScope></bibl>
                    </abv:example>
                    <abv:example xml:id="example_d1026e119">
                        <quote>bylæj ajnægmæ — gæpp! aftæ zǧory æxsærʒæn</quote>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                            <q>с обрыва на утес — прыг! так бежит водопад</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                            <q>jumping from the cliff on the rock, that's how waterfall is
                                running</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <bibl><biblScope>%sЦомак%s 64</biblScope></bibl>
                    </abv:example>
                    <abv:example xml:id="example_d1026e137">
                        <quote>ūrs fynk kalgæ sæx-sæxgængæ kommæ xawync æxsærʒæntæ</quote>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                            <q>разбрасывая белую пену, с шумом низвергаются в ущелье водопады</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                            <q>waterfalls are rushing down with noise and scattering white foam</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_Хар._Кадӕг"/><biblScope>58</biblScope></bibl>
                    </abv:example>
                </abv:exampleGrp>
                <etym xml:lang="ru">Перебой из *%iæf%i-%isærʒæn%i, как <ref type="xr" target="#entry_æxsærfars"/> ‘щека’ из *%iæfsærfars%i. В первой части %iæf%i-
                    из %iāр%i- ‘вода’ с ослаблением гласного в сложении. Во второй части — не
                    сохранившийся самостоятельно глагол *%isærʒ%i- ‘литься’, ‘падать’; ср.
                        <mentioned xml:id="mentioned_d1026e161" xml:lang="sa"><lang/>
                        <w>sarǰ</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:id="mentioned_d1026e166" xml:lang="sa"><w>sṛǰ</w>
                        <gloss><q>лить</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:id="mentioned_d1026e172" xml:lang="sa"><w/>
                        <gloss><q>давать течь</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:id="mentioned_d1026e178" xml:lang="ae"><lang/>
                        <w>harəč-</w>
                        <gloss><q>давать падать</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:id="mentioned_d1026e187" xml:lang="ae"><w>harəz-</w>
                        <gloss><q>лить</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:id="mentioned_d1026e193" xml:lang="gmh"><lang/>
                        <w>selken</w>
                        <gloss><q>падать (о жидкости)</q></gloss></mentioned>. Стало быть,
                    %iæxsærʒæn%i из *%iāp-sarjana%i-→*%iāfšārjana%i-. Сохранение %is%i после
                    %ix%i(%if%i) без обычного иранского перебоя → %ih%i говорит о том, что мы имеем
                    дело с очень старым сложным словом; ср. сохранение %is%i в <ref type="xr" target="#entry_æfsnajyn"/> рядом с <ref type="xr" target="#entry_najyn"/>.
                    По образованию ср. <mentioned xml:id="mentioned_d1026e205" xml:lang="fa"><lang/>
                        <w>ābšār</w>
                        <gloss><q>водопад</q></gloss></mentioned> из <mentioned xml:id="mentioned_d1026e213" xml:lang="fa"><lang/>
                        <w>āb</w>
                        <gloss><q>вода</q></gloss></mentioned> и <mentioned xml:id="mentioned_d1026e222" xml:lang="fa"><lang/>
                        <w>šār</w></mentioned> (от <mentioned xml:id="mentioned_d1026e227" xml:lang="fa"><lang/>
                        <w>šarīdan</w>
                        <gloss><q>шумно течь</q></gloss></mentioned>). Перебой %ifš%i →
                    %ixš%i(%ikṣ%i) наблюдается также в сакском, например <mentioned xml:id="mentioned_d1026e235" xml:lang="kho"><lang/>
                        <w>kṣārma</w></mentioned> из <mentioned xml:id="mentioned_d1026e240" xml:lang="kho"><lang/>
                        <w>*fšarma</w>
                        <gloss><q>стыд</q></gloss></mentioned>, ос. <ref type="xr" target="#entry_7fsarm"/>.</etym>
                <etym xml:lang="en">It is a version of *%iæf%i-%isærʒæn%i, like <ref type="xr" target="#entry_æxsærfars"/> ‘cheek’ from *%iæfsærfars%i. In the first part
                    there is %iæf%i- from %iāр%i- ‘water’ with the weakening of the vowel in a
                    complex word. In the second part there is the verb*%isærʒ%i- ‘poor’, ‘fall’
                    which did not remain as a seperate verb; cf. <mentioned xml:id="mentioned_d1026e255" xml:lang="sa"><lang/>
                        <w>sarǰ</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:id="mentioned_d1026e260" xml:lang="sa"><w>sṛǰ</w>
                        <gloss><q>poor</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:id="mentioned_d1026e266" xml:lang="sa"><w/>
                        <gloss><q>let flow</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:id="mentioned_d1026e272" xml:lang="ae"><lang/>
                        <w>harəč-</w>
                        <gloss><q>let fall</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:id="mentioned_d1026e281" xml:lang="ae"><w>harəz-</w>
                        <gloss><q>poor</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:id="mentioned_d1026e287" xml:lang="gmh"><lang/>
                        <w>selken</w>
                        <gloss><q>fall (of liquid)</q></gloss></mentioned>. Thus, %iæxsærʒæn%i is
                    from *%iāp-sarjana%i- →*%iāfšārjana%i-. The presence of %is%i after %ix%i(%if%i)
                    without a usual Iranian change → %ih%i tells that we are dealing with a very old
                    complex word; cf. the presence of %is%i in <ref type="xr" target="#entry_æfsnajyn"/> near <ref type="xr" target="#entry_najyn"/>. By
                    the derivation, cf. <mentioned xml:id="mentioned_d1026e299" xml:lang="fa"><lang/>
                        <w>ābšār</w>
                        <gloss><q>waterfall</q></gloss></mentioned> from <mentioned xml:id="mentioned_d1026e307" xml:lang="fa"><lang/>
                        <w>āb</w>
                        <gloss><q>water</q></gloss></mentioned> and <mentioned xml:id="mentioned_d1026e316" xml:lang="fa"><lang/>
                        <w>šār</w></mentioned> (from <mentioned xml:id="mentioned_d1026e321" xml:lang="fa"><lang/>
                        <w>šarīdan</w>
                        <gloss><q>flow noisily</q></gloss></mentioned>). The change %ifš%i →
                    %ixš%i(%ikṣ%i) is observed also in Khotanese, for example <mentioned xml:id="mentioned_d1026e329" xml:lang="kho"><lang/>
                        <w>kṣārma</w></mentioned> from <mentioned xml:id="mentioned_d1026e334" xml:lang="kho"><lang/>
                        <w>*fšarma</w>
                        <gloss><q>shame</q></gloss></mentioned>, Ossetic <ref type="xr" target="#entry_7fsarm"/>.</etym>
            </entry>
